  <a href="#1" id="1">
   The international community is becoming increasingly aware of the true magnitude of ethnic and political conflicts in the former Soviet Union.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Russia is concerned about conflicts close to its borders, about the safety of ethnic Russians living in those areas and about refugees fleeing to Russia.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   They argue that the international community should undertake peacekeeping missions in these areas as they have in other hotspots.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   These areas should be of concern to the international community both for humanitarian reasons
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   and because they risk provoking regional instability.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   If such peacekeeping missions are undertaken,
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   respect for the sovereignty of the newly independent countries must remain paramount.
  </a>
